cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with convolution operations involving large Vandermonde matrices, which are commonly used in information theory and numerical analysis. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation of the convolutions using Fourier-Motzkin elimination, which falls under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper includes a simulation and discusses connections with related matrices, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
